rComments: MAT1322, second calculus, is one of the hardest classes an engineer will take. of course he must mark hard and be ruthless (hard course), but he makes it so that if you work hard and put in effort, you will pass the course. very good at teaching, very good assignments for reviewing. allowed a cheat sheet for the midterm and exam. solid professor.

Worst Math Professor ever. He does not care about students and does not teach with live lectures, instead uses last year's prerecordings. Tests are brutal and ridiculously heavy loads compared to the last in-person exams. I have received A+ in other mathematic courses. This is the first time I ever received a lower grade than a B in a math course.

His first time teaching this course and it shows. Slaughtered us on the 1st midterm, but he pulled it together after that. He delivers the content well, calculus III is all practice. Course moves quickly, the vector calculus portions are probably the most important to know.

Guy Beaulieu est un excellent professeur qui a réussi la transition à l'enseignement en ligne. Les cours sont pré-enregistrés et l'heure de cours est une période de questions. Il est souvent disponible pour discuter en vidéo. Il explique très bien les concepts.

Alors la BIG RESPECT pour ce professeur. Lecture fluide très bonnes explications, il donne des devoirs chaque semaine cela peut paraitre mais c'est le seule cours ou j'étais à jour en plus il vous laisse des "how did i do" et 5 chances de refaire les devoirs. Le prof a bien maitriser la transition en ligne. Il peut meme vous appller pour vous expli

I was told Calc II was gonna be one of the hardest course in my program. Beaulieu's teaching made it manageable. One of the few profs at uni who properly transition to online teaching and landed on his feet.

Best math prof ever. After getting a D+ in calc 1 i kinda started to hate math but guy's lectures are so fun, i started to like calc again! He's a great lecturer and explains things so well! His notes are also so clear and easy to follow. Very approachable and he always give a clear outline of what to expect on tests.

He's not a bad professor per se, but his notes are unnecessarily complicated. If I wanted to learn word for word from the textbook then why would I ever come to class? Prep101 is the only thing that saved my grade. He's a nice guy, and enthusiastic about what he does, it's just that as a student that doesn't really help me at all :(

Best prof I've ever had. If you get the chance, take his class. He's super clear in explanations and his notes are extremely thorough, detailed and easy to comprehend. Evaluations aren't hard if you prepare enough, similar to other profs and previous years.

Dude guy below is the best of the Calc II profs. Lectures ensure you understand all the concepts covered & if not, he's very clear in explaining the question you have. Talks slower when he knows a confusing topic is being discussed to ensure clarity. Swag

Best. Prof. Ever. Not only does he answer emails in under 2 minutes, but also posts all lecture content, worked solutions, DGD questions, their worked solutions, and extra info on Brightspace. He's also super helpful and clear in class.

One of the best teachers I ever had at uOttawa. He explains the concepts very clearly and pick challenging questions from the slides to reinforce the explanation. He also cracks jokes in class, and is real easy-going and approachable. He always tells in advance what parts of the chapters will be tested in the midterms to help students prepare.

WORST math prof. AVOID AT ALL COST. LAZIEST MATH PROF I HAVE EVER SEEN. Takes notes directly from the textbook and uses slides to explain. His way of teaching a math class is horrible and doesn't have office hours And the WORST of all HIS FRENCH IS HORRIBLE. MIDTERMS MULTIPLE CHOICE!!!

WORST. No office hours. No reply to e-mails. Useless lectures (copy/pasted from textbook). Exams are all multiple choice -- NOT good (your method may be right, but you'll still get a 0 if you got the wrong number). No calculators! Most students aced the 1st midterm, so he destroyed us in 2nd/3rd midterms... Avoid if you care about your grade!
Just an all around great prof. Very thorough in lectures and gave practice questions with solutions for each of the lectures that filled in any gaps. If you pay attention, you'll do well.

Great lectures and interesting guy. Got tickled on my second midterm yet thoroughly understood the material. Questions are multiple choice a negative sign cost me 16% of my grade. Emailed him in regards to discussing the grading as I thought I was worthy of a better grade yet he never responded to 2 of my emails. Other than that he was good.

Really great prof! He spends a lot of time in class going over the process of solving different problems step-by-step. His notes are super clear and straightforward - he posts them all online! The course itself is not hard if you ask questions right away when you get confused and practice. Enjoyed being in his class!

His in-class examples go very in depth on how to solve the equations step-by-step and he's overall a very caring prof and has a super friendly personality. What made this class hard is the final.. really tough and it's worth 50%
Great prof! He posts all the in class examples, and outlines all test questions.
He is a really good teacher but the notes he uses are not very good so be sure to take your own notes. He is also a beauty

The lesser of the evils of MAT1332 profs. Going to class not mandatory as all powerpoints are posted online. Midterms were fair and represented the online homework quite well. Exam was super hard but with lots of practice not impossible. All midterms and exams are the same for all students, keep in mind.

He is a great prof! His lectures are different than other math courses as they're on slides, but he spends time going through examples so we can understand step-by-step what he did. He outlines everything on midterms and exams. He also spends time outside the classroom before and after class for extra help. Truly a great guy and a great prof!
I disliked his method of teaching off slides and He spends most of the time talking instead of solving problems.

Guy presents the concepts in an organized and straight-forward manner, and includes LOTS of short examples in class that allow you to understand the steps for solving any type of problem. The midterms were fair and the final was pretty easy, as long as you put in the effort throughout the semester to understand everything. Highly recommend!

Awesome teacher, the course tho is not awesome. Cal2 is the hardest course I have taken. but if you do your homework and understand it well, you'll probably pass. He is a great teacher, funny and energetic. midterm are really hard so prepare to study.
Young and enthusiastic prof. Homework reflected the material well and helped me prepare for the tests and final.
Good professor, helpful, undestanding. Evaluations reflect exactly what we saw in class, easy course for those who study and practice.

Best math professor I've ever had. He explains things very well and does in-class examples. The DGD before tests covers everything that will be on the test. He gives 3 tests during the semester which gives you the chance to make up for tests you haven't done well on. Marks fairly and wants you to succeed! Great prof!!
Sucks up to students. Ugh!
Best math teacher I've had at U of O, and very easy on the eyes :-)
One of the best teachers at U of O; has rollerblades which double as shoes
